BSR Europe, Kardan, Ness Technologies: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   F e r z i g e r
-- 
2011-04-04T06:09:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/bsr-europe-kardan-ness-technologies-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in the Israeli market. Stock symbols are in parentheses
after company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 0.8 percent to 1,331.82 in Tel Aviv.  BSR Europe Ltd. (BSR)  : The real-estate company said
it’s considering a 144 million-shekel ($42 million) bond sale in
Tel Aviv. BSR was unchanged at 7.662 shekels.  Kardan NV (KRNV)  : The Dutch-Israeli property investor
said it will post a 4 million-euro ($5.7 million) gain from GTC
Real Estate China Ltd.’s sale of its stake in Hangzhou
International Financial Center Co. Kardan increased 0.2 percent
to 19.02 shekels.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)  : Vector Capital Corp., a
San Francisco-based venture capital firm, is in advanced talks
to buy the computer-services provider for $300 million,
Calcalist reported, without saying where it got the information.
Ness climbed 2.6 percent to 22.78 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Ferziger in  Tel Aviv  at 
 jferziger@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
